cff-version: "1.2.0"
type: software

title: "Toy GPT: Embeddings-Based Next-Token Model trained on Analytics Corpus"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-04-02"

authors:
  - family-names: Case
    given-names: Denise M.
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6165-7389"
    affiliation: "Northwest Missouri State University, School of Computer Science and Information Systems, Maryville, MO, USA"

repository-code: "https://github.com/toy-gpt/train-500-embeddings"
url: "https://toy-gpt.github.io/train-500-embeddings/"
license: MIT

abstract: >
  A minimal, inspectable next-token prediction model using learned dense
  token embeddings trained on a technical analytics micro-lessons corpus.
  Introduces the embedding matrix as a first-class learned parameter,
  replacing the n-gram lookup tables used in earlier repositories (100-400).
  Backpropagation updates both the linear output layer and the embedding
  vectors, enabling generalization to unseen token combinations.
  Part of the Toy GPT educational series illustrating the progression
  from n-gram models to neural language model architectures.

